ozwell.s1: The two notes are essentially the same. They both describe the case of an 87-year-old woman who sustained a fall, resulting in a minimally displaced and impacted fracture of the proximal humerus. Both notes detail her past medical history, examination findings, investigations, and management plan. They also describe the subsequent development of thrombophlebitis of the external jugular vein and a deep vein thrombosis, along with the treatment provided. The notes are consistent in their content, with minor differences in wording and structure.
